We start by pulling the key information:

1. Free Cash Flow (FCF) is defined as:
  FCF = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities – Capital Expenditures  
  • From cash flow statement, “Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities” = –862455.97  
  • “Purchase of Fixed Assets” (the capital expenditure) = 0.00  
  Thus, FCF = –862455.97 – 0 = –862455.97

2. Return on Assets (ROA) is:
  ROA = (Net Profit) / (Average Total Assets)  
  • Net Profit (from income statement) = 1903401.82  
  • Total Assets at beginning = 13000000.00 and at end = 15528390.30, so  
   Average Total Assets = (13000000.00 + 15528390.30) / 2 = 14264195.15  
  Thus, ROA = 1903401.82 / 14264195.15 ≈ 0.1334 or 13.34%

3. Return on Equity (ROE) is:
  ROE = (Net Profit) / (Average Owner’s Equity)  
  • Net Profit = 1903401.82  
  • Owner’s Equity at beginning = 13000000.00 and at end = 14903401.82, so  
   Average Owner’s Equity = (13000000.00 + 14903401.82) / 2 = 13951700.91  
  Thus, ROE = 1903401.82 / 13951700.91 ≈ 0.1364 or 13.64%

4. Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio is:
  Operating CF to Net Income Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Net Profit)  
  = –862455.97 / 1903401.82 ≈ –0.4527  
  Rounded, this is –0.45

5. Net Profit Margin is:
  Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
  • Total Revenue (from income statement) = 4879769.51  
  Thus, Net Profit Margin = (1903401.82 / 4879769.51) × 100 ≈ 39.00%

6. Gross Profit Margin is:
  Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
  • Gross Profit (from income statement) = 2861769.51  
  Thus, Gross Profit Margin = (2861769.51 / 4879769.51) × 100 ≈ 58.65%

Now, we present the solution in the required JSON format:

{
  "solution": {
    "Free Cash Flow (FCF)": "-862455.97",
    "Return on Assets (ROA)": "13.34%",
    "Return on Equity (ROE)": "13.64%",
    "Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio": "-0.45",
    "Net Profit Margin": "39.00%",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "58.65%"
  }
}
